Methods

Every Method is structured the same! <method>(options)
memer.abandon(text).then(image => {
    //now you have a "BUFFER", for Discord create an attachment
      //const attachment = new Discord.MessageAttachment(image, "abandon.png");
      //<Channel>.send(attachment)
})

You just need to define Memer once, and then add the Method! Click at "Click here for DETAILS" to view example source Codes / Details

const Meme = require("meme-api");
const memer = new Meme();
â€‹
memer.<Method>(<OPTION>).then(image => { })

new Meme()

Initializes a new Meme which will return the Images!

//Import package
const Meme = require("meme-api");
//create new Meme() Class
const memer = new Meme();
â€‹

â€‹

abandon(text) => BUFFERâ€‹

Kind: instance method of Meme Returns: Buffer - Can be easily transformed to an Image

const Meme = require("meme-api");
const memer = new Meme();
â€‹
const text = "MEME API IS AWESOME";
â€‹
memer.abandon(text).then(image => {
    //now you have a "BUFFER", for Discord create an attachment
      //const attachment = new Discord.MessageAttachment(image, "abandon.png");
      //<Channel>.send(attachment)
})
